0.1.00: Perl 5.6.1, wxPerl 0.17, some standart libs


the VERSION number is like a date in the development timeline of the program,
no matter which part, a bigger number comes always after a smaller, pce 0.2
comes after pre 0.1.23

the PHASE number is like a stage of expansion; for all of you, who need a normal
editor just grab PHASE 1 in some future there will things like PHASE 2 with a
lot of space consuming toys not everybody needs

the PRE is the bundle off all needed 3rd party software to run the program.
normally ist is included in every full release, but for instance to settle with
pce 0.2.23 from windows to linux you may need pre 0.2 for linux


